# Task: Verify Bookshelf Web Application

## Checklist:
- [x] Navigate to http://localhost:3000
- [x] Wait 3 seconds for it to fully load
- [x] Take a screenshot of Cozy Billy (3-Col) and save it
- [x] Find and click the "Grand Wall (6-Col)" tab button near the top of the page
- [x] Wait 2 seconds
- [x] Take a screenshot of Grand Wall (6-Col) and save it
- [x] Evaluate containment of books inside shelves
- [x] Evaluate readability of titles
- [x] Evaluate visibility of category labels on wooden lips

## Findings and Observations:
1. **Containment of books inside shelves**:
   - Books sit cleanly and securely on the shelf floors within each compartment.
   - There is no overflow or clipping, matching the expected realistic physical shelf behavior.
2. **Readability of titles**:
   - Spines are beautiful. Wide books use legible horizontal paper labels.
   - Skinny books use vertical foil text rotated 90 degrees stretching along the length of the spine, ensuring text remains clear and readable without clipping or squishing.
3. **Visibility of category labels**:
   - Category labels (Movies, Places, Art, Social, Memories, Links, etc.) are highly visible, engraved beautifully on the front walnut wood lips, accented with brass/gold screwheads on the right. This keeps them clean and completely unobstructed by the books.
